data.chText: 用夹克衫改成的不成形的一件衣服
data.enText: a strange shapeless garment that had once been a jacket

data.text: clothes ♦ clothing ♦ garment ♦ dress ♦ wear ♦ gear

data.chText: 以上各词均指衣服、服装。
data.enText: These are all words for the things that you wear, such as shirts, jackets, dresses and trousers.
the things that you wear, such as shirts, jackets, dresses and trousers

data.chText: 指衣服，尤指某种类型的服装：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) clothes, especially a particular type of clothes

data.chText: clothing较clothes更正式，尤用以指某种类型的服装。clothes或clothing无单数形式，指一件衣服用a piece/an item/an article of clothing。
data.enText: Clothing is more formal than clothes and is used especially to mean ‘a particular type of clothes’. There is no singular form of clothes or clothing : a piece/an item/an article of clothing is used to talk about one thing that you wear such as a dress or shirt.

data.chText: 他穿着一件没样子的奇怪衣服。
data.enText: He was wearing a strange shapeless garment.

data.chText: garment只用于正式场合或文学语境，在日常生活中，一件衣服用a piece of clothing。
data.enText: Garment should only be used in formal or literary contexts; in everyday contexts use a piece of clothing .

data.chText: 指着装、衣着，尤指某种样式或某种场合穿的衣服：
data.enText: clothes, especially when worn in a particular style or for a particular occasion

data.chText: 我们在星期五可以穿便服。
data.enText: We were allowed to wear casual dress on Fridays.

data.chText: （通常构成复合词）指某种用途或场合穿的衣服，尤指于商店售卖的衣服：
data.enText: (usually in compounds) clothes for a particular purpose or occasion, especially when it is being sold in shops/stores

data.chText: 她的朋友都穿着最新款的衣服。
data.enText: Her friends were all wearing the latest gear (= fashionable clothes) .

value.def: A garment is a piece of clothing; used especially in contexts where you are talking about the manufacture or sale of clothes.

example.ex: Many of the garments have the customers' name tags sewn into the linings.
example.tran: 这些衣服有很多内衬上缝有顾客的姓名签。

value.tran: （一件）衣服（尤用于谈及服装的制作和销售时）
